results.name: Positive integers k that are the product of two integers ending with 6.
link: Stefano Spezia, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
program: isok(n) = {if (isok6(n), my(d=divisors(n)); fordiv(n, d, if (isok6(d) && isok6(n/d), return(1)));); return (0);} \\ _Michel Marcus_, Apr 14 2019
xref: Cf. A000400, A017341 (supersequence), A324298, A053742 (ending with 5).
